public class Member extends Object implements Comparable<Member>
Represents a member at the fitness chain. Allows for validation and storage of member information.

  • Constructor Details

    • Member

      public Member(String fName, String lName, Date dob, Date expire, Location location)
      Constructs Member object given expiration date. Stores identifying information about the member based on the parameters.
      Parameters:
      fName - the first name of the member.
      lName - the last name of the member.
      dob - the date of birth of the member.
      expire - the expiration date of the member's membership.
      location - the location of the member's gym.

    • Member

      public Member(String fName, String lName, Date dob, Location location)
      Constructs Member object for a new standard membership. Stores identifying information about the member based on the parameters, sets the expiration date for 3 months from the current date.
      Parameters:
      fName - the first name of the member.
      lName - the last name of the member.
      dob - the date of birth of the member.
      location - the location of the member's gym.

    • isValidDOB

      public boolean isValidDOB()
      Checks if the member's date of birth is valid. The date of birth needs to be before the current date.
      Returns:
      true if the person was born before today, false otherwise.

    • isAdult

      public boolean isAdult()
      Checks if the member is 18 years old or older. First checking if the birth year is more than 18 years before today. If it's a close call, checks specific birth month and day.
      Returns:
      true if the member is 18 or older, false otherwise.

    • isExpired

      public boolean isExpired()
      Checks if the member's membership is expired. Compares to see if the member's expiration date is before today.

      true if the member's membership is expired, false otherwise.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Member member)
      Compares the names of current member and another member lexicographically. Compares by last name first, then first names. Is not case-specific for names.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Member>
      Parameters:
      member - a member to be compared to with the current one.
      Returns:
      1 if the current member comes after the other lexicographically, 0 if the two members have the same first and last name, -1 if the current member comes before the other lexicographically.
